Quote:  <i>Te Hokowhitu A Tu</i> is the story of the Maori Pioneer Battalion in World War I... The title comes from the name given to the first contingent of "pioneers" who embarked from Wellington in 1915 bound for Egypt and Malta... In 1992, Major Wally Fraser found the lost colour of the Maori Pioneer Battalion in the Museum of New Zealand.
